Fixed values configuration

14) Production Outage Due to Wrong Configuration
Real-Time Scenario
Wrong ConfigMap values were deployed to production.

Impact
Production application downtime.

Resolution
Rolled back deployment immediately
Added approval gates
Added GitOps validation

15) SSL Certificate Expired
Real-Time Scenario
Production application became inaccessible over HTTPS.

Root Cause
Certificate renewal failed.

Resolution
Renewed certificate
Added monitoring alerts before expiry

Strong Interview Closing Line
“In real-time DevOps projects, pipeline failures are usually not just tool issues. Most failures happen because of dependency conflicts, infrastructure drift, configuration mistakes, security controls, deployment strategy problems, or environment inconsistencies. My approach is always to first identify the exact stage of failure, analyze logs carefully, isolate the root cause, resolve the issue with minimal downtime, and finally implement preventive automation so the same issue does not happen again.”

